where Prad and RD represent the out-coupled power to the radiation mode and the luminous reflectance. (1 – RD) works as the CR. The definition of γ reflects the desired qualities of OLEDs for high out-coupled optical power into the radiation mode and low reflectance of the ambient light and is presented in Fig. 2b.

